          "markdown": {
            "es": "> Aquí se define **media licencia**. Si dominas las cuatro familias —**Term, Whole Life, Universal Life y Variable**— y sabes leerlas en un caso, ganas un bloque enorme de preguntas. La idea madre que ordena todo el capítulo: **¿es temporal o permanente?** y **¿quién carga el riesgo de inversión, la aseguradora o tú?**\n\nConceptos de este capítulo:\n\n- 4.1 **Seguro de Término (Term Life)** — level, decreasing, increasing, ART, renewable, convertible\n- 4.2 **Vida Entera (Whole Life)** — continuous, limited-pay, single-premium\n- 4.3 **Universal Life (UL)** — flexible premium, Opción A vs Opción B\n- 4.4 **Variable Life y Variable Universal Life (VUL)** — separate account, licencia de valores\n- 4.5 Pólizas especializadas — **Joint (first-to-die) vs Survivorship (second-to-die), Indexed UL, Modified/Graded, Family, Juvenile**\n\n> 🧭 **Mapa mental antes de entrar:**\n> ```\n> TEMPORAL ─► Term (sin cash value, barato, caduca)\n> PERMANENTE ─► Whole Life (todo garantizado, rígido)\n>            ─► Universal Life (flexible, transparente)\n>            ─► Variable / VUL (tú inviertes, tú arriesgas)\n> ```\n\n---",
            "en": "> This chapter defines about **half the license**. If you master the four families — **Term, Whole Life, Universal Life, and Variable** — and know how to read them in a scenario, you win a huge block of exam questions. The main idea that organizes the whole chapter is: **is it temporary or permanent?** and **who carries the investment risk, the insurance company or you?**\n\nConcepts in this chapter:\n\n- 4.1 **Term Life Insurance** — level, decreasing, increasing, ART, renewable, convertible\n- 4.2 **Whole Life Insurance** — continuous, limited-pay, single-premium\n- 4.3 **Universal Life Insurance (UL)** — flexible premium, Option A vs Option B\n- 4.4 **Variable Life and Variable Universal Life (VUL)** — separate account, securities license\n- 4.5 Specialized policies — **Joint (first-to-die) vs Survivorship (second-to-die), Indexed UL, Modified/Graded, Family, Juvenile**\n\n> 🧭 **Mental map before starting:**\n> ```\n> TEMPORARY ─► Term (no cash value, cheaper, expires)\n> PERMANENT ─► Whole Life (everything guaranteed, rigid)\n>           ─► Universal Life (flexible, transparent)\n>           ─► Variable / VUL (you invest, you take the risk)\n> ```\n\n---"
          }
