          "markdown": {
            "es": "> Aquí se junta toda la **fiscalidad** que viste suelta en capítulos anteriores. El examen ama este tema porque parece complicado, pero se reduce a **tres preguntas**:\n>\n> 🔑 **1) ¿Se grava el beneficio por muerte? (casi nunca) · 2) ¿Se grava lo que sale EN VIDA? (solo la ganancia sobre la base) · 3) ¿Es un MEC? (entonces, cuidado).**\n>\n> Si dominaste \"¿este dinero ya pagó impuesto o no?\" del Cap. 8, este capítulo es tu **vuelta de la victoria**.\n\nConceptos de este capítulo:\n\n- 10.1 **Tributación del beneficio por muerte (Death Benefit)** — income tax y estate tax\n- 10.2 **Valores en vida**: cash value, dividendos, préstamos, rescate y la **base (cost basis)**\n- 10.3 **MEC — Modified Endowment Contract**\n- 10.4 **Primas y seguro de negocios**: deducibilidad, group term \\$50k, key person, transfer-for-value\n- 10.5 **1035 Exchange y nociones de estate/gift tax**\n\n---",
            "en": "> This chapter brings together the **tax rules** you saw in earlier chapters. The exam likes this topic because it seems complicated, but it comes down to **three questions**:\n>\n> 🔑 **1) Is the death benefit taxable? Almost never for income tax. 2) Is money taken out WHILE ALIVE taxable? Only the gain above basis. 3) Is it a MEC? Then be careful.**\n>\n> If you understood \"has this money already been taxed?\" from Chapter 8, this chapter is your victory lap.\n\nConcepts in this chapter:\n\n- 10.1 **Taxation of the Death Benefit** — income tax and estate tax\n- 10.2 **Living values**: cash value, dividends, loans, surrender, and **cost basis**\n- 10.3 **MEC — Modified Endowment Contract**\n- 10.4 **Premiums and business insurance**: deductibility, group term $50k, key person, transfer-for-value\n- 10.5 **1035 Exchange** and basic estate/gift tax ideas\n\n---"
          }
