            "en": "| # | Term | One-line meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| 18 | Owner | Controls the policy and all rights |\n| 19 | Insured | Life covered; death triggers payment |\n| 20 | Beneficiary | Receives proceeds, no control unless irrevocable |\n| 21 | Primary beneficiary | First to receive proceeds |\n| 22 | Contingent beneficiary | Receives if primary does not survive |\n| 23 | No living beneficiaries | Pays to the **estate** and probate |\n| 24 | Revocable beneficiary | Can be changed without consent, default |\n| 25 | Irrevocable beneficiary | Vested; must sign to change/borrow/assign/cancel |\n| 26 | Per stirpes | Deceased person's share passes to descendants |\n| 27 | Per capita | Only surviving beneficiaries at same level share |\n| 28 | Common disaster | Insured presumed to survive → pays contingent |\n| 29 | Spendthrift clause | Protects proceeds from beneficiary's creditors |\n| 30 | Third-party ownership | Owner ≠ insured, requires insurable interest |"
